RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE NOVEMBER 19 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 19 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races With W inning Earnings Of $4,500 Or Less Not Considered Or Claiming Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL BONUS raced off the pace on the inside early, continued around the turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear. BEBOP BABY pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and in upper stretch and chased the winner home late. ATLANTIC PRINCESS raced off the pace between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the two path and improved position in the lane. LYRICAL tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and weakened in the final furlong. WORKIN NINETOFIVE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the early going, came around the turn in the three path and was outkicked in the stretch. WINDOW SHAKER led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and tired in the lane. CELTICS WILDCAT stumbled and lost his rider leaving the gate, was caught by an outrider following the race and walked off. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REJECTION HURTS raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far bend and kicked clear in the stretch. RAMBLINGAMBLINMAN saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path and chased the winner home in the lane. FOUND JORDAN trailed the field while saving ground through the opening half mile, began to move up while racing in the two path around the turn and continued to improve position in the stretch. TOTAL SURPRISE saved ground at the back of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and gained ground mildly in the lane. MR INSENSITIVE saved ground around the first bend, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the second turn and weakened in the final furlong. TAHKODHA KNIGHT saved ground around the first turn, stalked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend and faded in the stretch. POSITIVE PETEY raced in the two path early, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and tired in the lane. LL'S CLASSY DUDE raced off the pace in the three path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ON SPEED DIAL stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and kicked clear in the stretch. NORTHERN ANGEL raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the turn from the three path and chased the winner home in the lane. SASSY MAMA chased the pace setter up the backstretch, continued around the bend in the two path and kept on in the lane. CLOUDLESS BLUE hopped up leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack early, came around the turn in the two path and improved position from there. LIL SASSY JONES bumped lightly with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and weakened in the stretch. MIDNIGHT JOY trailed the field through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and made no bid.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOCK IT DOWN saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch and around the far bend and drew off in the stretch. BADGER KITTEN raced in the two path early, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and kept on to the finish. HURRICAIN HUNTER saved ground around the first turn, tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and finished evenly. A THOUSAND DREAMS raced in the three path around the first bend, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and weakened in the final furlong. MERLIN'S SISTER trailed far behind the field through the opening half mile, saved ground around the turns and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 11500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 26 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HI HO CHEERIO raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole, dueled in upper stretch and kicked clear in the stretch. DILLON ROCKS reared and bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn, dueled in upper stretch and chased the winner home in the final furlong. CANNONBALL COMIN led the way through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend, was caught in upper stretch and chased on to the wire while drifting midly late. BOTANY raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane. I WILL STAND was bumped by the horse to his inside and reared up at the start, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and made no bid. COCO BRAVADO raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the turn and faded further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 7 1/2F Turf CR: 73. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. (Rail at 15 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JEWEL AZUL saved ground at the back of the pack through the opening half mile, began a bid from the five path coming around the far turn dueled in the lane and got up for the win late. WITHHERBOOTSON raced in the two path early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the second turn and dueled to the wire to narrowly miss. TANTIMA raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the four path and improved position in the stretch. BARBARA ROHLOFF saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn and weakened in the final furlong. DURA THE EXPLORER raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path and showed no kick. BALIMOS raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, navigated the far bend from the two path and made no bid. AIN'TNOSWEETIE saved ground around the first bend, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and was empty in the stretch. GIVE EM SHADE raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and tired in the lane.
